    • Method Detail

      • find

        Network.FindInvocation find(java.util.List<java.lang.String> networks)
        Returns network information for the specified vCenter Server networks. The key in the return value Map is the network identifier and the value in the Map is the network information.

        Invocation Result:
        Network information for the specified vCenter Server networks. The key in the return value Map is the network identifier and the value in the Map is the network information. The key in the return value Map will be an identifier for the resource type: Network.

        Parameters:
        networks - Identifiers of the vCenter Server networks for which information will be returned. The parameter must contain identifiers for the resource type: Network.
        Returns:
        instance of Network.FindInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described find operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        NotFound - if no datastore can be found for one or more of the vCenter Server network identifiers in networks
        Unauthorized - if you do not have all of the privileges described as follows:
        • Method execution requires System.Read.
        • The resource Network referenced by the parameter networks requires System.Read.
